%h2 Class07 Lab Answer:
%h2 Use wget to copy d1d2.herokuapp.com into d1d2

%p This was easy.

%p The wget utility has a -r option which fits this use-case.

%p After I wget the site, I copy its contents up a level so http-server can see and serve it:

.syntax
  %pre
    %code.bash
      cd ~/d1d2
      wget -r   d1d2.herokuapp.com
      rsync -av d1d2.herokuapp.com/ ./

